      "how": "The GTM Engine output becomes the blueprint for your growth model. Each gear maps to a team (Insight = Research, Value = Product Marketing, Motion = Demand Gen, Execution = Sales, Feedback = CS). Misaligned gears = broken revenue engine.",
      "example": "Notion's GTM Engine: Insight (teams waste time switching between 5 tools) → Value ('all-in-one workspace') → Motion (product-led, templates, community) → Execution (self-serve + enterprise sales) → Feedback (template gallery + community). Each gear reinforces the next.",
