                'Nordstrom: A customer returned a set of car tires to Nordstrom. Nordstrom doesn\'t sell tires. The employee accepted the return anyway, gave a full refund from the register. This story became legendary. It\'s unexpected (they don\'t sell tires), creates a gap (why would they do that?), and sticks because it violates the schema of "what a store does." The story spread without any marketing budget.',
