                'Boeing 727: Instead of "build the best passenger plane" (abstract), they set ONE concrete target: "Seat 131, fly Miami\u2192NYC, land on Runway 4-22 at La Guardia." Every engineer, designer, and supplier could picture this. The concrete target aligned thousands of decisions. The 727 became Boeing\'s best-selling plane for decades.',
