                    name: 'IX. Binary Search', icon: '🔍', fill: '#F0F9FF', stroke: '#0EA5E9', text: '#0369A1', cp: 'O(log n) · O(1)', tier: '⭐ Beginner',
                    py: 'def binary_search(arr, target):\n    lo, hi = 0, len(arr) - 1\n    while lo <= hi:\n        mid = (lo + hi) // 2\n        if arr[mid] == target: return mid\n        elif arr[mid] < target: lo = mid + 1\n        else: hi = mid - 1\n    return lo  # insertion point\n\n# Binary Search on Answer\ndef bs_answer(lo, hi):\n    while lo < hi:\n        mid = (lo + hi) // 2\n        if feasible(mid): hi = mid\n        else: lo = mid + 1\n    return lo',
